    "summary": "Henk is an ambitious and independent researcher in specialized in Modeling of Biological Systems. He has strong quantitative skills and uses these skills together with his curiosity and discipline to unravel the biological mechanisms of life. He participated in the cross-disciplinary \u201cReduced methane emission of dairy cows\u201d TI Food and Nutrition project team of Animal Nutritionists, Geneticists, Microbiologists and Dairy Scientists. Throughout this project, he focused on modeling of rumen fermentation physiology in cattle and predicting enteric methane emissions. Upon finishing his PhD, He spent more than 3 years at the Animal Science department at the University of California, Davis (USA). Henk currently works at the Laboratory of Systems and Synthetic Biology at Wageningen University, and is involved in the \"Me, my diet and I\" project. He contributes to the development of a Digital Twin for predicting personalized Glucose and Triglyceride dynamics in blood plasma for which he applies various dynamic modelling approaches. Henk's most recent publication is \"Inhibited Methanogenesis in the Rumen of Cattle: Microbial Metabolism in Response to Supplemental 3-Nitrooxypropanol and Nitrate\". (https://doi.org/10.3389/fmicb.2021.705613)",
