            "description": "This project aims at increasing knowledge about methane production by dairy cows in order to reduce the ecological footprint of dairy production. For this purpose, we are developing an indicator for methane emission from individual cows; we are exploring the genetic variation in methane emission between cows; we are characterizing the composition and functioning of microorganisms in the rumen of the cow; and we are developing mechanistic models to improve the understanding of how methane emission is influenced by the interaction between the genetics of the cow, the microorganisms in the rumen of the cow and cow feedstuffs.",
